# Community Detection in Social Networks: A Comparative Study

## ğŸ“Œ Overview

This project explores **community detection in social networks** using graph mining algorithms. The objective is to compare multiple community detection techniques on a real-world dataset: the Facebook combined ego-network dataset from Stanford SNAP.

By combining centrality analysis and community detection methods, the project uncovers the structural organization of the network, identifies influential nodes, and evaluates how different algorithms partition the graph into meaningful communities.

---

